---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="About the MyGO Knowledge Graph Archive">
  <section class="about-page">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      The MyGO Knowledge Graph Archive is a searchable, interconnected knowledge network
      for <em>BanG Dream! It's MyGO!!!!!</em> and <em>Ave Mujica</em>.
    </p>
    
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>
      Every piece of content — characters, songs, events, documents, paragraphs, and sentences — 
      becomes a node in the knowledge graph. Nodes are connected through relationships, 
      allowing you to traverse the entire knowledge network without reaching dead ends.
    </p>

    <h2>Content Sources</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Anime Episodes</li>
      <li>Game Stories</li>
      <li>Official Interviews</li>
      <li>Official Radio</li>
      <li>Official Blog Posts</li>
      <li>Official Event Reports</li>
      <li>Live Reports</li>
      <li>Magazine Interviews</li>
      <li>Staff Interviews</li>
      <li>Voice Actor Interviews</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Technology</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a></li>
      <li>Graph visualization by <a href="https://js.cytoscape.org">Cytoscape.js</a></li>
      <li>Search powered by <a href="https://github.com/nextapps-de/flexsearch">FlexSearch</a></li>
      <li>Hosted on <a href="https://pages.github.com">GitHub Pages</a></li>
      <li>Static site generation — no backend required</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contributing</h2>
    <p>
      Content is stored in Git. Contributors can add markdown files, edit metadata, 
      add annotations and tags, and submit Pull Requests. The site rebuilds automatically.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>